<h3>Cursor or GitHub Copilot, in-editor coding assistant</h3>
<div class="tool-card">
  <span class="price-tag">Cursor: $20/month (~&#8377;2,005 with GST)</span>
  <span class="price-tag">Copilot: $10/month (~&#8377;1,003 with GST)</span>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Tab-complete code suggestions, function generation in-context, multi-line edits, refactoring shortcuts.</p>
  <p><strong>Honest take:</strong> If you write code for 4+ hours a day, an in-editor assistant pays for itself in saved keystrokes. Cursor uses Claude under the hood with a better editing UI; Copilot is cheaper and integrates with VS Code natively. Pick one, not both.</p>
