<h2>What about open source models?</h2>

<p>Engineers in India ask this often. Yes, you can run Llama 3.x or Mistral locally, but for daily commercial work the time cost (model setup, GPU, slower inference) is rarely worth the savings unless you have data residency or compliance reasons. Use a paid hosted model and route per-request via OpenRouter if you want flexibility.</p>

<h2>How to pay for AI tools as an Indian engineer</h2>

<p>For team plans, your company's payment will go through normally. For personal subscriptions, use a forex card or Niyo Global, Indian debit cards get rejected often. Detailed payment workarounds: <a href="/guides/pay-for-ai-tools-india/">5 ways to pay for AI tools from India</a>.</p>

<h2>Tax and GST notes</h2>

<p>If you are a freelancer or consultant invoicing clients, the AI tool subscription is a deductible business expense. Save the GST invoice from the provider (most issue them via email or in the dashboard).</p>

